                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24074.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Fletcher reports rioting at Chang-sha on 13th and 14th, and says governor’s
                    yamen, two English and one Norwegian mission burned. Adds that foreigners are
                    safe; that foreign office assures him that there is no reason for anxiety; and
                    that three British gunboats are on their way to Chang-sha.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
